The paper deals with computational geometry problems related to convex hulls and subsets, which are typical topics in the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The algorithms presented in the paper involve data structures and optimization techniques, which are also relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The problem of finding subsets with maximum area or weight can be seen as a combinatorial optimization problem, which is related to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The paper also mentions the Erdős-Szekeres problem, which is a classical topic in the cs.GT (Graph Theory) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents algorithms with time and space complexity bounds, which are relevant to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
